Description:
Why build?
This brick veneer home offers three bedrooms and open plan living. The galley kitchen has stainless steel appliances including gas cooktop, underbench oven and dishwasher and overlooks the meals and lounge area. The master bedroom has walk in robe and ensuite with separate shower, vanity and toilet. The remaining two bedrooms offer built in robes. The family bathroom has separate bath, shower compartment and vanity. Climate throughout is controlled by gas ducted heating and split system to lounge/meals area. Externally there is an outdoor entertaining area, double garage and small rear yard. For investors, this property has been previously rented out at between $310 - $320 per week. Why be inconvenienced with building a brand new home when this one is only a few years old and ready to be moved into today! Worth an inspection.

Description:
Incomparable To The Rest
Perhaps one of Cobram's finest home is being offered for sale. In one of the most sought after locations. This 2 Storey residence was built to perfection and overlooks the mighty Murray River
Let's talk about the layout cleverly designed with 3 spacious bedrooms upstairs as well as the main bathroom. The master bedroom is located on the ground level and features a great walk in robe & en suite with stunning 6ft claw foot bath, double vanity & separate shower.
They say the kitchen is the heart of the home and this kitchen is spectacular featuring a great open plan with lots of cupboards surrounding, Island bench, walk in pantry, Hidden dish washer & microwave cupboards. Both Gas & electric elements. Opening onto the entertaining area overlooking the pool
Formal living & dining area, games/TV room, office, great size laundry. Ducted gas heating throughout & two separate evaporative cooling systems on each level.
Outside is pure paradise in ground swimming pool & spa. Built in veranda with opening electric louvers. 15x6x3M shed with rear access via River Road. Fantastic size shed which can accommodate up to 8 Cars!
Gazebo overlooking the Cobram-Barooga bridge & river, in ground sprinkler systems, solar panels with built in batteries
Rare opportunity to own your own piece of paradise Call 5872 1255 7 days

Description:
Fantastic investor or first home
This three bedroom home offers open plan living with renovated laminated kitchen with gas cooktop and underbench oven and overlook both the meal and lounge areas with polished timber flooring connecting the spaces. Two of the bedrooms have built in robes. The family bathroom has also been updated with bath, shower and vanity. Climate is controlled throughout with a split system and wood heater. Externally there is a great shed with a bonus room that could be utilised for a fourth bedroom for the growing teenager. There is also a really good sized rear yard. This home is in a great location and is currently tenanted at $270 per week.

Description:
Federation charm meets contemporary finesse of today
This gorgeous family home built by quality Builder, Tim Sessions was completed in 2010 and offers approximately 30sqs of luxury living. Upon arrival you are greeted by the stunning timber floors, that connect all the living zones of the home from the formal lounge to the front to the oversized family/meals/kitchen area to the rear. The statement piece in the kitchen is certainly the oversized island with stone benchtops and waterfall edges. It comprises quality stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, walk in pantry and pot drawers. Double timber french doors then lead out to the outdoor entertainment area making this home ideal for those who love to entertain with family and friends. The Master bedroom is generous in size and offers boxed bay window, walk in robe and ensuite with double sized shower, separate toilet and large vanity with stone benchtops. The remaining four bedrooms are also generous in sized, with two offering built in robes and two with walk in robes. The Laundry offers an abundance of storage and bench space with the addition of a huge walk in linen. Everything has been meticulously considered with the design of this family home including ducted reverse cycle heating and cooling throughout. You will not be disappointed with an inspection of this property.

Description:
The Historic "Eaton"
Timeless heritage and classic charm. This historic residence with 11 foot ceilings was built in by the Eaton family in the 1920's has been recently restored and renovated. A fantastic oppurtunity to secure a character home on approx. 981 square metres of land, just one block back from the main street of Cobram.
Features a spacious kitchen and meals area with a stainless steel gas stove, walk in pantry, large breakfast bar, island bench and a brick fireplace with gas log fire. Adjoining living area with sliding doors to the outdoor entertaining area. Separate formal lounge with a fire place, French doors and polished timber floors. Three generous bedrooms plus a generous study, the main bedroom with a walk-in robe and ensuite, and another bedroom with builtin robes. Reverse cycle split system air conditioning and ceiling fans throughout.
Huge 10m x 5m enclosed outdoor entertaining area with a bistro blinds, TV point, open fireplace, and a built-in barbecue, rangehood and benches with a sink. 4 vehicle carport, 9m x 6m 3-bay colorbond shed with roller doors, concrete floor and power, and rear entry.
Re-stumped, re-roofed, painted, all new period style aluminum windows, upgraded wiring, new plasterboard and paint - all the work is done! Don't miss out, call today.
